-- Germany’s SPD Proposes Panel to Combat Skills Shortage, SZ Says
-- B y   J a m e s   K r a u s
-- 2012-05-22T23:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-22/germany-s-spd-proposes-panel-to-combat-skills-shortage-sz-says.html
Germany ’s opposition Social
Democratic Party has proposed a special panel in the federal
chancellery to help overcome professional skill shortages,
 Sueddeutsche Zeitung  reported, citing an interview with Hubertus Heil, the party’s deputy chairman, in a preview of an article
due to appear today.  The panel would be comprised of representatives of
industry, unions as well as the federal labor agency and
regional and community associations, the newspaper said.  The party cited shortages of highly skilled as well as
intermediate skilled professionals in industry as well as
scientific professions, nursing and child-care centers as
reasons for their concern, SZ reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
James Kraus in London at 
